Global, Turkcell, Turkish Airlines: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-06-23T06:40:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/global-turkcell-turkish-airlines-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 815.28, or
1.3 percent, to 61,217.96 yesterday.  Global Yatirim Holding AS (GLYHO)  : The diversified
Turkish holding’s broker Global Menkul Degerler AS, known as
Global Securities, sold a 25 percent stake for 16.5 million
liras ($10 million) in an initial public offering yesterday,
after getting 41 million liras of demand, Hurriyet reported,
citing Global Securities chief executive officer Gokhan Ozer.
Global Yatirim fell 2 kurus, or 1.6 percent, to 1.26 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI), Turkey’s
biggest mobile-phone operator, will hold an extraordinary
 shareholders’ meeting  on Aug. 11, rescheduling an April 21
annual meeting which ended without any decisions, including a
dividend payment, due to disputes among owners, it said in a
statement to the Istanbul bourse after the market closed
yesterday. Turkcell rose 4 kurus, or 0.4 percent, to 9.04 liras.  Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AO: The carrier known as
Turkish Airlines aims to be among Europe’s biggest airlines by
increasing the number of its destinations to 230 in two years
from almost 190, Hurriyet reported, citing chief executive
officer Temel Kotil. Turkish Airlines dropped 6 kurus, or 1.4
percent, to 4.16 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  